  0<f'(x)<\frac{1}{x^{2}}  
\lim_{n\to\infty}(f((n+1)^{2})-f(n^{2}))=0
f
(0,\infty)
a,b\in (0,\infty)
a<b
c
a<c<b
f(b)-f(a)=f'(c)(b-a).
n
f((n+1)^2)-f(n^2)=f'(c_n)((n+1)^2-n^2)
c_n
n^2<c_n<(n+1)^2
(n+1)^2-n^2=2n+1
\frac{1}{c_n}<\frac{1}{n^2}
n
\left|f((n+1)^2)-f(n^2)\right|=\left|f'(c_n)\right|\left|(2n+1)\right|<\frac{2n+1}{c_n^2}<\frac{2n+1}{n^4}
\lim_{n\to\infty} \left[f((n+1)^2)-f(n^2)\right]=0
0\leq \int_{n^2}^{(n+1)^2}f'(t)dt=f((n+1)^2)-f(n^2) \leq \int_{n^2}^{(n+1)^2}\frac 1{x^2} dx = \frac{-1}x\mid_{n^2}^{(n+1)^2}=\frac 1{n^2}-\frac 1{(n+1)^2}.
\xi
n^2 < \xi < (n+1)^2
f((n+1)^2) - f(n^2) = f'(\xi)(2n + 1) < \frac {2n + 1} {\xi^2} < \frac {2n + 1} {n^4}
